								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>The <b>History of the Prophets and Kings</b> (Persian: تاریخ طبری, Arabic: تاريخ الرسل والملوك <i>Tarikh al-Rusul wa al-Muluk</i>, popularly known <i>Tarikh al-Tabari</i>) is a historical <a href="Chronicle" title="Chronicle">chronicle</a> written in Arabic by Persian<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> author and historian <a href="Ibn_Jarir_al-Tabari" title="Ibn Jarir al-Tabari" class="mw-redirect">Ibn Jarir al-Tabari</a> died 310H (838-923) from the Creation to AD 915, and contains detail concerning <a href="Muslim_history" title="Muslim history" class="mw-redirect">Muslim</a> and the <a href="History_of_the_Middle_East" title="History of the Middle East">history of the Middle East</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
<td>
<div id="toctitle">
